<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>pull on the heartstrings • pull the strings</xh5><p> <i>pull on the heartstrings</i>—(also: tug at the heartstrings) stir deepest feelings or affections: The group’s songs have the ability to <u>pull on the heartstrings</u> of listeners and carry elevating messages of hope and warmth.</p><p><i>pull the strings</i>—(also: pull strings) 1. secretly exert influence and power: Tony’s uncle had the title of boss but it was obvious to all of us who really <u>pulled the strings</u>. 2. obtain smth. through the influence of people one knows: Is it possible to get anything done around here without <u>pulling strings</u>?</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>pull the string of the shower-bath</b>—(rare) cause smth. concealed to be made known suddenly: Why can’t he <u>pull the string of the shower bath</u>? Why is it all locked up, refrigerated? Because he’s a priest, a mystery monger.</p> </entry>
